description: A walk around the Botany Bay Foreshore's shared bike paths with an optional extention through Kamay Botany Bay National Park.

markers.description: Get the train to Wolli Creek using transportnsw.info.
From the station follow the footpath through the mall straight ahead. There are amenities along the mall.
On the other side of the mall follow the roundabout ahead to the Princes Hwy.
Cross the Princess Hwy at the traffic lights and continue into Cahill Park.
There is a toilet block at the entrance to the park.
Follow the footpath through Cahill Park along the riverside.
At the other side of the park follow Rockwell Ave ahead around the dog park.
After the dog park follow the footpath along Marsh St to the right.
At Flora Street use the traffic lights to cross Marsh St.
From the crossing follow the shared path along Marsh St to the right.
Follow the bike path to the left before the M5.
Follow the shared path along the power lines.
Follow the underpass to the right underneath the M5.
From the gate follow Eve St to the left.
From the end of Eve St follow the shared path through Riverine Park.
At the end of the park follow the shared path to the left along the canal.
Follow the shared path to the right across the bridge.
Follow the shared path and boardwalk along the sports fields.
There are toilet blocks along the sports fields.
At the end of the sport fields follow Bestic St left across the bridge.
On the other side of the bridge follow the footpath left to the playground.
From the playground continue on the footpath past the community gardens.
Cross the carpark at the Kyeemagh Boat Ramp. There is a toilet block at the picnic area.
From the boat ramp follow the shared path along the shorefront.
Follow the shared path underneath the Endeavour Bridge.
After the bridge follow the shared path to the beach.
Follow the shared path along the beach reserve.
There's toilet blocks along the foreshore.
From the end of the park at the hippo statue, continue straight along The Grand Parade.
There's toilet blocks along the foreshore.
Follow the esplanade along Brighton Le Sands Beach.
There's toilet blocks along the foreshore.
Follow the esplanade along Ramsgate Beach.
There's toilet blocks along the foreshore.
Follow the Esplanade around Dolls Point.
Follow the esplanade past the sailing club.
After the sailing club follow the esplanade to the left along the shore.
There's toilet blocks along the foreshore.
At Sans Souci Point follow the esplanade to the Captain Cook Bridge.
Follow the right path up the ramp of the bridge.
Cross Captain Cook Bridge along the shared path.
Follow the path off the bridge to the left and follow Woodlands Rd.
Enter the Tarent Point Foreshore Reserve on the left.
Follow the shared path along the shorefront.
From the toilet block at the intersection follow the sign to Cronulla to the left.
Continue following the the shared path past the Anglers Club.
Follow the boardwalk across the mangroves.
From the end of the boardwalk follow the shared path along the fenceline of the marina.
At the intersection follow the sign to Kurnell left.
Follow the shared path past the industrial estate.
Follow the shared path across another boardwalk.
Follow the shared path around the apartment building. There is a cafe between the two buildings.
After the buildings follow the shared path right under the overpass.
At the end of the shared path follow Captain Cook Dr to the left to the Sharks Stadium.
Cross Captain Cook Dr at the stadium and continue left. There are shops a little past the stadium.
Cross Woolaware Rd and continue straight on Captain Cook Dr.
Follow the shared path past the Cronulla Golf Course.
At the roundabout cross Elouera Rd and continue straight on Captain Cook Dr.
At the roundabout cross Trinity St and continue straight along Caption Cook Dr.
-20km At the roundabout follow Trinity St to the right for a shortcut to Cronulla.
From the roundabout follow Brolga Ave to the right.
From the corner of Brolga Ave follow the access path between the houses to the dunes.
Follow the shared path to the right to the carpark.
From the end of the footpath, continue on the shared bike path along Captain Cook Dr.
At the sports fields continue straight along Captain Cook Dr.
There is a viewing platform across the wetlands on the left side of Captain Cook Dr.
At the roundabout continue straight on Captain Cook Dr.
From the bus stop continue straight on Captain Cook Dr.
At the Desalination Plant continue straight along Captain Cook Dr.
At Kurnell start following the footpath along Captain Cook Dr.
There are amenities a short distance in Kurnell on the left side of Captain Cook Dr.
From the intersection follow Silver Beach Rd to the left.
At the intersection follow Prince Charles Pde to the right along the beach.
From the corner of Prince Charles Pde, follow the footpath along the shore into Kamay Botany Bay National Park.
From the right side of the path follow the steps up the embankment.
Follow the trail markers to the Visitor Information Centre.
The obelisk monument is to the left of the path.
Follow the path through the presentation space behind the Visitor Information Centre.
There are toilets outside the Visitor Information Centre.
From the front entrance of the Visitor Information Centre, cross the car park.
From the far end of the carpark follow the sign to the Banks-Solander Track.
Cross the road and follow the signs to Cape Solander past the gate.
There is a self guided tour on the left side of the Yena Trail.
Follow the sign on the right to Cape Solander.
At the intersection with the firetrail follow the sign left to Cape Solander.
At the intersection with the Pipeline Link follow the trail marker right to Cape Solander.
Follow the trail markers to Cape Solander across the rocky sections.
Follow the trail to the car park at Cape Solander.
From the carpark follow the boarwalk right along the coastal cliffs.
Follow the trail markers to the Cape Baily lighthouse.
Follow the trail markers along the rocky sections.
Follow the trail markers around the Tabbigai Gap to the Cape Baily Lighthhouse.
From the other side of the Tabbigai Gap follow the Cape Baily Track to the lighthouse.
Follow the boardwalk through the sandy dune section.
Follow the last section of the boardwalk to the foot of Cape Baily Lighthouse.
The light is a warning not to sail a ship into the steep cliffs of the coast. Let it also be a reminder not to fall off the same.
markers.title: The Guiding Light
markers.instruction: Visit this location to earn the mystery trophy

markers.description: From the lighouse follow the dirt track through the coastal heath.
Traverse the rocky section to Potter Point.
From the end of the rocky platform follow the gravel the rest of the way to Potter Point.
From Poter Point follow the gravel path to the carpark.
From the carpark follow the sign to Cronulla Railway Station.
From the sign follow the gravel path to the beach.
Follow the a short distance.
Climb the trodden path over the dunes on the right side of the beach.
Follow the sandy trail through the dunes to the left.
If the access to the dunes cannot easily be found, climb up at the old pipeline instead.
From the pipeline follow the sandy trail along the coast.
At Boat Harbour follow the sandy trail right to the start of the beach.
Follow the trail off the headland onto the beach.
Follow the beach around Boat Harbour.
Follow the ocean along the car beach. Watch out for traffic.
From the fences at the end of the car beach follow the trail into the dunes on the right.
Follow the access trail through the dunes along the fenceline.
From the open grassy spot follow the gravel road away from the  beach.
At the intersection follow the trail to the left.
Follow the trail up the Cronulla Sand Dunes.
From the viewing platforms across the Cronulla Sand Dunes continue following the trail.
Follow the trail past the gate to the carpark.
Follow the shared path along the left side of the carpark.
There are toilets at the Wanda Beach Surf Club.
From the surf club follow the shared path along Mitchell Rd.
Follow Prince St along the beach.
From the restaurants at the end of the beach follow the esplanade along the shore.
Follow the esplanade to Cronulla Beach.
Follow the footpath through the beach reserve to the carpark.
From the carpark cross Gerrale St and follow Beach Park Ave to the station.
Plan your return trip from Cronulla at transportnsw.info.
